        COOLOCELOTS CHART REVIEW

        hey pals and gals, its coolocelot101. tonight im gonna give you a review, but before we get into the new entries, ill observe the moves around the top 40.

        head & heart is number 1 for 6 weeks now... you know, im kinda tired of this song now! its still pretty good, but its time to move on from it. it sold 62k overall units this week. i see dancing in the moonlight is dropping away, that because thats still a 10/10 from me. on deck rebounds massively into the top 40 too! lets get into the top 40 entries.

        BTS - DYNAMITE (#3)
        i know bts and i really hate them as artists, and i know this is their first full-english song and its led on itunes... well, finally, a decent bts song for a change! of course, theres still issues with their vocal delivery, especially when jungkooks falsetto in the chorus isnt great and i cant understand them. however, better qualities come in with the really groovy beat, and feel-good lyrics! itll take me a while to actually like bts, but this one is at least passable. light 6/10.

        HEADIE ONE FT AJ TRACEY & STORMZY - AINT IT DIFFERENT (#4)
        headie did a great job on both and only you freestyle, aj tracey is just really fire as an artist and stormzy put out one of my favourite records of 2019. theyve come together to create something fire! i like that high pitched vocal layering, especially when the accompanying trap beat is awesome! then we get the deliveries... headie goes completely in on this, while aj brings a speedy flow which reminds me of rain, which is one of my favourite uk rap songs this year, and stormzy... do we not know him for bringing amazing verses?! my only nitpick is that each verse of theirs is too short, but that doesnt stop the song from being good. decent 8/10, it could go up!

        24KGOLDN FT IANN DIOR - MOOD (#11)
        so 24kgoldn was announced as a xxl freshman this year, but i dont know if that was the reason why this leapt up the charts. that doesnt matter, because this is actually really good though! i like the guitar strums at the start, and like with rockstar, it fits well with the bass-y trap beat. i really like iann diors singing delivery, but sadly 24kgoldn doesnt sound all that good in my opinion. we also have lyrics about a lover playing games and 24kgoldn wont play by her rules anymore and theyre well written to me. nice job, both of you. strong 8/10!

        quick interruption to announce vera lynns land of hope and glory is back at number 17! this follows after a bbc proms controversy, and its number 1 on itunes as we speak.

        CONAN GRAY - HEATHER (#22)
        well, this went up really fast, didnt it? this is a chilled song and i like it. to start, his vocals are very breathy and mellow, to calm you instantly, as he sings about his love for this girl but someone else likes her more. i really like the guitar strums in the verses, and the production suddenly comes up to a massive climax in the chorus, before going back to the mellow guitars in that final chorus. yeah, this was really chilled and i can see myself coming back to this - strong 7/10!

        CLEAN BANDIT FT MABEL & 24KGOLDN - TICK TOCK (#36)
        so this is 24kgoldns 2nd appearance on this review. im happy that clean bandit are back as i love their music... but this was very underwhelming. i like the beat that brings a sense of bounce to the song, but their usual violin comes in at the most random time possible and sounds very squeaky! im not really a fan of mabels delivery which is surprising, as shes a great singer, and tick tock, tick tock comes in at some of the worst possible times. and 24kgoldn sounds more autotuned than he should be... nah, clean bandit have put out much better than this. light 5/10!

        on the albums chart, the killers score their 6th number 1 album with imploding the mirage! it debuted at number 1 with 50k chart sales.

        the rest of the top 5 is: shoot for the stars, aim for the moon by pop smoke (4-2), folklore by taylor swift (2-3), the neon by erasure (new at 4), and legends never die by juice wrld (non mover at 5)

        so yeah, decent week overall. i enjoyed putting this review together, and i hope you enjoyed reading. have a good weekend! :)
        P.S. my top 25 favourite songs of the week will come later tonight.

        WEEKLY CHART REVIEW (28/08/2020 - 03/09/2020)

        (Negative)

        1) Lighter dropped back even more today, but while its chances of #1 are almost completely gone, Im hoping itll get a resurgence thanks to the acoustic version that was released today (Ella Henderson sounds way better in the new version!).

        2) I think we can rule out Top 10 peaks for both Dancing In The Moonlight & Heaven On My Mind, which absolutely !

        3) Blinding Lights is starting to drop faster! Yes, its had an amazing run here, but I still adore it as much as I did back when it first came out, so I was always going to hate seeing it go.
        Whats Love Got To Do With It just lost momentum out of nowhere! I sincerely hope its not out of the Top 40 by next week.

        4) Unfortunately, I think Rain On Me is going to drop out of the Top 40 in the next chart!
        Cardigan continues to drop fast, but at least Radio 1 played it during the chart show again today!

        5) The worst thing about this chart is Dua Lipa having a rough week, with both Hallucinate & Levitating both dropping out of the region today.

        (Mixed)

        1) Wap looks like it might take the lead next week, given how much it closed the margin today! Itd become both Cardi Bs & Megan Thee Stallions first #1 single in the UK, which would continue the trend of no artists scoring multiple #1s in 2020.

        2) Both Savage Love & Go Crazy leave the Top 10! I still dont hate these songs somehow, but I know theyll get on my nerves sooner or later.

        3) Looking For Me is holding up incredibly well, but it really stalled here after the sudden boost it got last time!

        4) Heather blasted into the chart out of nowhere! The sentiment in the lyrics is sweet, but its just a shame that the rest of the song is a completely snoozefest. This was very nearly in the negative section, but the content just about saved it from getting there!

        5) The Woo absolutely crashed this week! I thought this was because of ACR at first, but no, it just had a terrible week apparently.

        6) Rockstars declines are starting to get really steep now! Its still a decent trap song, but its been here for long enough now.

        7) On Deck re-entered to a new peak, which Im indifferent on after revisiting it. Its a fine enough drill song, but nothing extraordinary.

        (Positive)

        1) Head & Heart held on to #1 despite close competition! I think this could be the last week it spends there, but at least it got the record for the longest consecutive chart-topper of 2020 so far.

        2) Dynamite had extremely dominant download figures, allowing it to debut in the Top 3! Ive actually been following K-Pop for a few years (before anything other than Gangnam Style hit the chart from the genre), so its really satisfying to see a Korean group do so well here, especially when Dynamite is very fun, bright & uplifting. This is their first song entirely in English!

        3) Aint It Different also joins it immediately beneath it! Honestly, this is one of my favourite UK rap collaborations of the year so far. All three artists here bring incredible flows & the production is particularly menacing! This is exactly what Im looking for in a brag-rap banger, haha.

        4) Along with West Ten, AJ Tracey is back with two songs in the Top 10 once again!

        5) I knew Mood was going to become big this week, but I didnt expect it to rank this high! This is definitely one of the most fun trap songs Ive heard in ages. Im rooting for this to keep climbing!

        6) The legendary Vera Lynn made the Top 20 thanks to huge sales! It that her cover of Land Of Hope & Glory wasnt played by Radio 1, but its a classic nonetheless.

        7) Midnight Sky mightve dropped from last time, but it held up far better than I was expecting it to!

        8) Tick Tock sneaks in as the lowest of the six new entries today! Clean Bandit have always been able to mix classical instrumentation & EDM production very well, which is also an awesome fit for both Mabel & 24kGoldn here (he had a good week, didn;t he?). I hope this is a slow burner!

        9) On the albums chart, The Killers debuted at #1 with over a 6x lead! Honestly, while many people love this group for just Mr Brightside, Im a fan of many other hits of theirs. Glad to see them still doing so well!

        Hope you enjoyed my review everyone! Have a good weekend. :)
